  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">U&amp;I- Build Resilience to save lives and properties of people in Arab Countries</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Arab region has a long history of dealing with natural hazards and severe climate conditions including droughts, floods and extreme temperatures. Today, the convergence of such longstanding challenges with more recent economic and social developments, including urbanization and population growth, has heightened the region&apos;s vulnerability. The fragility of socio-ecological systems are shown to be either irreversible or their recovery may take long time. The project aims to provide instruments including local DRR management strategy, training packages and communication material to strengthen the resilience and improve the readiness of communities in pilot areas prone to NHs.</narrative>
  </description>
